</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" link="#23238e">
<a href="../index.html"><img alt="[OpenBSD]" height="30" width="141" src="../images/smalltitle.gif" border="0"></a>
<p>
<h2><font color="#e00000">OpenBSD spamd</font></h2>

<hr>

<p>
OpenBSD's
<a href="https://man.openbsd.org/?query=spamd&amp;sektion=8">spamd(8)</a>
is a SPAM deferral daemon which rejects false mail in a very efficient way.
<br>
A variety of databases exist here which can be specified in the
<a href="https://man.openbsd.org/?query=spamd.conf&amp;sektion=5">/etc/mail/spamd.conf</a>
file, and loaded using
<a href="https://man.openbsd.org/?query=spamd-setup&amp;sektion=8">spamd-setup(8)</a>.
<p>

<ul>
<li><a href="nixspam.gz">Nixspam</a><br>
The <a href="https://www.heise.de/ix/nixspam/dnsbl_en/">Nixspam suspicious
sources list</a> formatted for spamd.
<P>
OpenBSD mirror location:
<a href="nixspam.gz">https://www.openbsd.org/spamd/nixspam.gz</a>
<p>

</ul>
<p>

<hr>
<a href="../index.html">
<img height="24" width="24" src="../back.gif" border="0" alt="Main page">
</a>
<br>
