1.14
log
@spamd.conf moved to /etc/mail, reflect change here too. OK beck@@.
@
text
@a32 11
Some of the URLs below point to www.openbsd.org locations.  That means
that some of the OpenBSD www mirrors located around the world will
also contain these files.  Hence, it is possible to edit
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=spamd.conf&amp;sektion=5">
/etc/mail/spamd.conf</a>
and replace www.openbsd.org with, for instance, www.de.OpenBSD.org.
The actual www.openbsd.org links are local links; meaning, those files
may be accessible from this mirror directly; for instance, if you were
using www.de.OpenBSD.org
<p>

